      "writtenOn": "2019-09-11T14:02:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: for L and XL changes of new code, it can be handy to include in the commit message (or gerrit \"send off\" message) a \"guide to review\".\n\nThis guide can be as simple as:\n\"\"\"\n1. look at the types in File A\n2. Read the tests in File B_test\n3. Read the implementation in File B\n4. Look at everything else\n\"\"\"\nThe guide doesn\u0027t need to be 20+ steps, just a \"start here and here\", otherwise I (and maybe others) default to first file first, or have to go on a scavenger hunt ourselves. \n\nor \n\"\"\"\nPS 1 and 2 adds ... \nPS 3+ adds ...\n\"\"\"\n\n(the latter only works out nicely depending on how the code was written)\n\n\nYou don\u0027t need to retroactively add one for this change, just keep it in mind for the future.",
      "revId": "2f3bd08c0981991789d64e0e29480c64d100524b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
