      "writtenOn": "2019-09-11T14:02:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Run returns an error, so we should return an error also.\n\nFor large services, having a panic/os.Exit deep in the code can make it hard to determine why the service \"crashed\" or stopped.  Not to mention os.Exit and tests don\u0027t play nicely.\n\nAs a rule of thumb, keep any Fatalf/Exit calls in a main.go, so it is clear where the executable will stop (you only have to check one file then).",
