      "writtenOn": "2019-09-11T14:02:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This double map structure is a bit awkward. Our number of deployments is small, so lets store them as []deploymentWithOptions.\n\nThen, let\u0027s put that slice into a struct as an unexported field so no client messes with them and so we can change our mind how we hold onto the data if we want.\n\ntype Deployments struct {\n   deployments []deploymentWithOptions\n}\n\nThis means we could probably get rid of the ForAll helper (or at least make it unexported).\n\nAs mentioned on main.go, a Contains() method would be useful here.",
